  <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Users\jeff.ruby\Desktop\DITA\exersice\flowers\topic\Flowers by Season.dita" xtrc="title:1">Flowers by Season</title>
  <body class="- topic/body " xtrf="C:\Users\jeff.ruby\Desktop\DITA\exersice\flowers\topic\Flowers by Season.dita" xtrc="body:1">
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\jeff.ruby\Desktop\DITA\exersice\flowers\topic\Flowers by Season.dita" xtrc="p:1">The various climatic changes that occur in cyclic pattern are termed as 'Seasons'. There are
      four general seasons occurring on Earth - Spring, Summer, Autumn and Winter. Flowers and
      seasons are intimately bound to each other. When Most of the flowers are season-specific.
      However, some flowers are found throughout the year, not particularly affected by changing
      seasons.</p>
  </body>
